question: Thoughts on the Cyrus/Jonah/TJ storyline?
answer:
It was the best of the 4 plots for sure (the other three being the Bexie date, the Ambi party, and the Bandi tension).

Some of the acting felt a little off in some scenes but whatever. I really liked seeing TJ and Jonah talking about their issues. I’m always here for the show destroying toxic masculinity stereotypes.

But I feel like the route the show took in order to get those two to talk about their issues was meh. The whole grudge plot felt pretty shoehorned in tbh (though Asher narrating the flashback was gold). I get what the show was going for (highlighting that worrying about small things is part of anxiety) but I feel like the stakes for the Jonah/TJ plot could’ve been raised a bit more so that resolution could have a better pay off.

TLDR: it was the best of the subplots but I think this show needs to be 42 minutes instead of 22-24 in order to allow storylines in an episode room to breath

summary: Really really minor detail but I kinda wish they would've used "location services" being on or whatever rather than "spyware."...
question: Really really minor detail but I kinda wish they would've used "location services" being on or whatever rather than "spyware." Not because the show wasn't clear that Andi was the one to text, but just because casually throwing in the idea of parents putting spyware on their kids phone not to address it makes me just a tiny bit uncomfortable. Maybe because I have friends whose parents really would Do That and I don't want it normalized even as a lie? Idk, not that big a deal though
answer: I mean I get that. I’ve had friends with abusive parents who do that kinda thing BUT I don’t think it would have made Bowie seem as strict and believable if he had played it down like that either lol.
